**Theme Application:**
- All Syncfusion components use the Material-3 theme: import `@syncfusion/ej2/material3.css`
- Dark mode: add `.e-dark-mode` class to the root element — Syncfusion Material-3 responds automatically.
- Custom token overrides go through Theme Studio or CSS variable overrides using the `--color-sf-*` token system.

**Component States:**
- Every component must render all Syncfusion built-in states: default, hover, focused, active, disabled, loading.
- Do not override Syncfusion state styles — use token overrides only.
- Disabled state is handled by Syncfusion via the `disabled` prop — do not manually grey out.

**Accessibility:**
- All Syncfusion Material-3 components are WCAG 2.2 / Section 508 / WAI-ARIA compliant by default.
- Do not remove ARIA attributes added by Syncfusion.
- Keyboard navigation is built into all Syncfusion components — do not reimplement it.

### C. Do / Don't

**Do:**
- ✅ Use Syncfusion Material-3 Figma Kit components in all design files.
- ✅ Map every Figma component 1:1 to its Syncfusion React/JS code counterpart.
- ✅ Apply Material-3 theme CSS globally — never per-component.
- ✅ Use Theme Studio to generate custom theme CSS from modified tokens.
- ✅ Use `.e-dark-mode` class for dark theme switching.
- ✅ Leverage Syncfusion's built-in RTL support via `enableRtl: true` globally.

**Don't:**
- ❌ Do not build custom components when a Syncfusion equivalent exists.
- ❌ Do not use any other UI library (MUI, Ant, Chakra, shadcn, Radix).
- ❌ Do not override Syncfusion internal class names directly.
- ❌ Do not import Fluent, Bootstrap, or Tailwind theme — Material-3 only.
- ❌ Do not disable Syncfusion's built-in accessibility attributes.
- ❌ Do not use Syncfusion component markup outside its documented API.

### D. MCP Usage Guidance
- When generating any UI element, first identify its Syncfusion Material-3 component equivalent.
- Reference the Syncfusion UI Kit Figma file for design specs: `https://www.figma.com/community/file/1454123774600129202`
- When generating code, always use the Syncfusion component import path: `@syncfusion/ej2-react-*` (React) or `@syncfusion/ej2-*` (JS).
- Enable RTL globally at app root: `L10n.load()` + `setCulture('ar')` + `enableRtl(true)` for Arabic interfaces.
- Apply Material-3 CSS at root level — never inline per component.
- When a Figma frame references a Syncfusion component, extract its variant/state from the Figma layer name and map it to the corresponding Syncfusion prop.
